  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package embeds W-AR-05: the primary validation result omits a comparedAgainst link; a secondary result references a comparator dataset derived from ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions rather than CPB operating conditions, introducing a subtle but material inference mismatch for the declared COU.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-rh-criterion",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-identifies-worst-case-hemolysis-cpb",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-gcbp-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
