      "rationale": "The primary validation activity (PIV comparison) was conducted at a single operating point within the VAD benchmark envelope. The validation team assessed the overlap with the CPB COU as adequate at Gradation 2 on the grounds that the impeller geometry, nominal flow rate at the lower operating point, and turbulence regime are shared. Differences in fluid properties (blood vs. glycerol-water analogue), pulsatility, and the RPM sweep range specific to CPB were acknowledged in the factor rationale but were not subjected to a formal similarity analysis or extrapolation uncertainty quantification."
